    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Simon the jeweler just opened his store and needs a nice storefront logo. His store specializes in diamonds, so he wants a diamond as a logo.<br><br><strong>With a given size, create a diamond logo for Simon.</strong><br><br>A diamond of size 5 would look like this:<br><pre style=\"font-family: monospace\"></pre><pre style=\"font-family: monospace\"><br>  *  <br> *** <br>*****<br> *** <br>  *  <br></pre><pre style=\"font-family: monospace\"></pre><br>Every line of the diamond has equal amount of characters, that means the trailing space characters should be kept in each line of the output.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\">An integer <var>size</var>, which describes the size of the diamond.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">The ASCII diamond.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &lt;= <var>size</var> &lt;= 16<br><var>size</var> is odd</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">5</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">  *  \n *** \n*****\n *** \n  *  </pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
